animal_concentrations.Value: Analysis of seal blubber from grey seals (Halichoerus grypus) found in Sweden in 2008 detected decamethylcyclopentasiloxane levels of 9-24 ng/g wet weight(1).

fish_seafood_concentrations.References: (1) ECHA; Search for Chemicals. Decamethylcyclopentasiloxane (CAS 541-02-6) Registered Substances Dossier. European Chemical Agency. Available from, as of Aug 12, 2015: https://echa.europa.eu/ (2) Kierkegaard A et al; Environ Sci Technol 45: 5936-42 (2011) (3) Kierkegaard A et al; Chemosphere 93: 774-8 (2013)
fish_seafood_concentrations.Value: Fish collected from Lake Erie during the fall/summer months of 2009 (common shiner, yellow perch, emerald shiner, trout perch, white perch freshwater drum and walleye) contained mean decamethylcyclopentasiloxane concentrations of 14-36 ng/g wet weight and 179-386 ng/g lipid(1). Smelt and brown trout collected from Lake Mjosa Norway in Sept-Oct 2010 contained nmean decamethylcyclopentasiloxane concentrations of 18700 and 4000 ng/g lipid respectively(1). Fish collected from the Oslofjord Norway during a 2010 study (Atlantic herring, coalfish, commond sole, Norway pout, European hake, starry skate, haddock, pollock, cod) contained mean decamethylcyclopentasiloxane concentrations 43.4-1435.4 ng/g wet weight and 1455-26106 ng/g lipid(1). Flounder samples collected from six sites in the lower Humber estuary in England in 2009 contained decamethylcyclopentasiloxane concentrations of 12-269 ng/g wet weight(2). Herring (Clupea harengus) collected off the Sewdish coast in 2007 contained decamethylcyclopentasiloxane concentrations of 15-720 ng/g lipid wet(3).

Available from, as of Aug 12, 2015: https://echa.europa.eu/ (2) Kierkegaard A et al; Environ Sci Technol 45: 5936-42 (2011) (3) Zhang Z et al; Arch Environ Contam Toxicol 60: 201-11 (2011)
sediment_soil_concentrations.Value: SEDIMENT: Sediments collected from the Oslofjord Norway during a 2010 study contained mean decamethylcyclopentasiloxane concentrations of 137.1-149.3 ng/g wet weight(1). Sediments collected from six sites in the lower Humber estuary in England in 2009 contained decamethylcyclopentasiloxane concentrations of 59-263 ng/g dry weight(2). Twenty-five sediment samples collected from various sites of the Songhua River, China in 2009 contained decamethylcyclopentasiloxane concentrations of 3.40-155 mg/g with a mean concentration of 52.7 mg/g(3).
